item.title: Demodulation of the 5G NR downlink – Daniel Estévez
item.description: At the end of July, Benjamin Menkuec was commenting in Twitter about some issues he had while demodulating a 5G NR downlink recording. There was a lively discussion in which other people and I participated. I had never touched 5G, but had done some work with LTE, so I decided to take the chance to learn more about the 5G physical layer. Compared to LTE, the changes are more evolutionary than revolutionary, but understanding what has changed, and how and why, is part of the puzzle.

item.title: zkSecurity partners with ZPrize to make you win hundreds of thousands of dollars!
item.description: There’s one big competition in ZK, and it is called ZPrize. Every year, ZPrize rewards contestants who come up with the most performant implementations for a series of challenges. The goal is to push the limits of what’s possible with ZK, and to make sure that the best implementations are open-source and available to everyone. This year, zkSecurity is proud to announce it’ll play the role of one of the three external architects for the competition, hosting the High Throughput Signature Verification ZPrize category.
